title: My Bible History: New Testament
creator: Louis Laravoire Morrow
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of My Bible History: New Testament, by Louis Laravoire Morrow. Read by Maria Therese. A short, simple New Testament Bible History for children, but which can also be enjoyed by adults alike. Starting with St. John the Baptist, and running through the beginning years of the Church, the sections cover Our Lord's birth, public life, miracles, death, resurrection and more. This is the companion volume to My Bible History: New Testament - by the same author. (Summary by Maria Therese) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
